SIMPLE: somatology
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Somatology
<hw>So`ma*tol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>sw^ma</grk>, <grk>sw`matos</grk>, body + <ets>-logy</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The doctrine or the science of the general properties
of material substances; somatics.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A treatise on the human body; anatomy.</def>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The science which treats of
anatomy and physiology, apart from psychology.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Anthropol.)</fld> <def>The consideration of the
physical characters of races and classes of men and of mankind in
general.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Somatome</ent>⟦br⟧
